Ability of a system to continue operating without interruption when one or more of it's components fail.

- Both HA & FT have same objective that system runs all the time without any disruption
- FT can be a improved version of HA, as it can tolerate any component failure or data loss by having redundant resources beyond what is typically needed.

- Circuit breaker
- Bulkhead
- Load Balancing
- Service Balancing
- Broadcasting Messages
- Active-Active, Active-Passive
- Place replicas in different racks
